Photo, Rough Landing The gas tanks of a single-engine Malibu aircraft ruptured 
and the plane's tires blew out during a hard landing at Van Nuys Airport Monday 
morning. Officials said the craft lost power and struck the landing strip about 
11 a.m.; Photo, The impact, estimated at five times harder than normal, bent 
the plane's wings and damaged the tires and fuel tanks, located in the wings.; 
Photo, Firefighters sprayed foam on the runway to prevent leaking gasoline from 
igniting. The airport's main runway was closed nearly two hours. The pilot and 
a passenger, whose names were not available, were not injured. BOB CAREY / Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
