<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 500 gallons of sewage overflowed from a manhole in Del Mar on Monday, 
according to County Health Services Department officials. 
</P>
<P>
The spill began at 1:15 p.m. when a manhole at Lamista and Camino Del Mar 
became blocked for unknown reasons. 
</P>
<P>
The sewage flowed into the street and emptied into the ocean from a storm drain 
at the end of Ninth Street before the spill was stopped at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Signs warning of the contamination have been posted at several points along the 
storm drain, and will remain for 24 hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
