<P>
SAFE STREETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I feel President Bush should be commended for using the military as a police 
force in Panama to make the streets safe for people to come out of their homes. 
</P>
<P>
If we (in the U.S.) are going to use the military as a police force (spend 
taxpayers dollars) to make streets safe in a foreign country, what about the 
streets in America such as Washington, D.C., Los Angeles, Detroit, etc? We have 
more crime and killings in American cities on a weekend than Panama has in a 
year. 
</P>
<P>
It is time we take back the streets and parks of America. 
</P>
<P>
President Bush, we have Noriegas in most cities of America who are also common 
criminals and need to be brought to justice. 
</P>
<P>
MILT BURDICK 
