</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The average price of an existing house sold in metropolitan San Diego area was 
a record $220,751 in December, a 21% increase over the average cost in 
December, 1988, according to a recent survey of transactions by members of the 
San Diego Board of Realtors. 
</P>
<P>
The median price of resold homes was $174,000, or 11% higher than the median 
price a year previous. 
</P>
<P>
The median price is the level at which half of all houses were sold for more 
and the rest for less. 
</P>
<P>
Member realtors sold 1,292 houses in December, or 16% more than the 1,111 units 
sold in the comparable month a year ago. For the 12 months ended in December, 
total resales were 20,223, or 5% more than the 19,243 houses sold in all of 
1988. 
</P>
<P>
The record average price set for December ended an eight-month period during 
which the average prices remained flat, staying within a range of between 
$217,000 and $209,000. The median price, however, is still less than the 
$175,000 median price of April, 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
