<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: FORTUNE PETROLEUM REVISES EARNINGS SHARPLY LOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fortune Petroleum, an Agoura Hills oil and gas concern, revised its earnings 
sharply lower for the third quarter of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Citing a recalculation of its depletion, depreciation and amortization figures, 
Fortune said it earned $4,000 in the quarter that ended Sept. 30, instead of 
the $34,000 profit it originally reported. The company's year-earlier loss of 
$26,000 was unchanged, as was its revenue, which climbed to $230,000 from 
$194,000 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of 1989, Fortune posted a revised loss of $36,000, 
instead of the $6,000 loss it initially reported. The company did not revise 
its year-earlier loss of $34,000, nor did it alter its nine-month revenue, 
which rose to $734,000 from $651,000. 
</P>
