<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Baccarat Table to Be Installed at LACMA: A dazzling crystal table, made in the 
mid-19th Century at the Baccarat French crystal house, is being installed today 
in the Los Angeles County Museum of Art's decorative arts galleries. The 
5x3-foot table is a longterm loan from Los Angeles collectors Arthur and 
Rosalinde Gilbert. 
</P>
<P>
The crystal table formerly belonged to Liberace. Asprey galleries of London 
bought it for $44,000 in Los Angeles at an April, 1988, auction of the late 
singer's collection. The Gilberts subsequently purchased the table from Asprey 
for an undisclosed price. Reproductions of baccarat tables are occasionally 
offered for sale but, according to the museum, the only other known original is 
in the collection of the Corning Museum of Glass in Corning, N.Y. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
