American Airlines Had Best On-Time Record: The airline with the best on-time 
flight performance in November was American and the carrier with the worst 
on-time flight performance was USAir, the Transportation Department reported. 
The 12 largest U.S. carriers reported that 78% of their flights operated on 
time in November, below their 79.5% on-time performance in October. The 
department said consumers registered 1,125 complains against airlines in 
November, down from 1,143 in October. 
