<HEADLINE>
<P>
LATVIAN WHO FLED U.S. FACES WAR CRIMES TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MUENSTER, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An alleged Nazi war criminal who fled the United States to avoid possible 
deportation to the Soviet Union will go on trial in West Germany later this 
month, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Boleslav Maikovskis, 86, a Latvian, will go on trial Jan. 18 charged with 
murder and complicity in the shooting deaths of 170 villagers in Audrine, 
Latvia, during World War II, according to a statement by the state court in 
Muenster. 
</P>
<P>
Maikovskis, a former resident of Mineola, N.Y., fled the United States in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
