<P>
NEW MEXICO STATE'S HILL GOES TO BANK TO BEAT UNLV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS CRUCES, N.M. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Hill's 16-foot bank shot with five seconds left Monday night gave New 
Mexico State an 83-82 Big West Conference victory over No. 7-ranked Nevada Las 
Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
The Aggies, off to their best start since a Final Four appearance in 1969-70, 
are 12-1 and 3-0 in the Big West. 
</P>
<P>
UNLV dropped to 9-3 and 4-1. 
</P>
<P>
Hill finished with 19 points, and guard Randy Brown, who carried the Aggies 
offensively in the first half, scored a season-high 27. 
</P>
<P>
UNLV had 24 points from David Butler and 12 each from Larry Johnson and Greg 
Anthony. Johnson had a final attempt to avoid the upset, but his 12-foot 
turnaround jump shot hit the front of the rim as the Pan American Center crowd 
of 12,719 celebrated the Aggies' first victory win ever over the Runnin' 
Rebels. 
