<P>
Electrical grounding -- A story in Sunday's Real Estate section on replacing 
two-prong electrical outlets with three-prong receptacles is applicable only 
for a grounded electrical system. Many older homes do not have a grounded 
system and installing three-prong receptacles would create a potentially 
hazardous situation. If you are considering such a conversion and don't know if 
you have a grounded system, contact a licensed electrician. 
</P>
