</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 10 residents of a Chatsworth condominium complex were evacuated this 
morning when a fire broke out in the garage area, the Los Angeles Fire 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The fire in the 10200 block of Larwin Avenue was reported about 1:42 a.m., and 
about 20 firefighters had the flames controlled in 18 minutes, said Capt. 
Robert Robar. 
</P>
