<P>
'TEDDY Z' OUT, 'CITY' SITCOM IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Famous Teddy Z" is out and a new Valerie Harper sitcom titled "City" will 
be on CBS Monday nights, the network announced today. 
</P>
<P>
"Teddy Z" will have its final airing Jan. 13, and "City" will make its debut at 
8:30 p.m. Jan. 29. 
</P>
<P>
In "City," Harper plays the city manager of an unnamed metropolis. The show's 
heroes are the bureaucrats, the only thing standing between the people and the 
politicians. 
</P>
<P>
Her character, Liz Gianni, is a widow with a 19-year-old daughter who has 
returned home after dropping out of college. She also has an intense desire to 
make things better. 
</P>
<P>
CBS said that "The Famous Teddy Z" will return to the network at a time and 
date to be announced. 
</P>
