<DATELINE>
<P>
CHARLOTTE, N.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When a fire alarm went off at one of Charlotte's fanciest restaurants, actress 
Brooke Shields joined other patrons outside in the rain until it proved to be a 
false alarm. 
</P>
<P>
Once it had been determined the alarm had been set off by a coffee maker, 
Shields returned in bright spirits. 
</P>
<P>
"I love trauma," she said. "I feel closer to you all. We've bonded." 
</P>
<P>
Shields was in town to promote a line of curling irons, hair dryers and other 
products bearing her name. 
